snippet.title: ASICS Women's GT 2150 Running Shoe - Top Deal Review
snippet.description:
ASICS Women's GT 2150 Running Shoe - Top Deal Review
Toegevoegd door yodyeled 2 jaren geleden
http://t.co/qJFBxJh - ASICS Women's GT 2150 Running Shoe - Top Deal ReviewRunning shoes are a very subjective thing, I understand. Not every foot is the same and not every running shoe is built the same but Asics are by far the best brand I have run in, and I've run in a lot of different brands of shoes (Nike, New Balance, Adidas). They are the only shoe that I have taken out of the box and worn for the first time in a 10k with no issues whatsoever. This is a very supportive and springy shoe while being incredibly lightweight. The ventilation is great and the shoe conforms to my foot as if custome made. I have a narrow foot and normal to high arch, and I run about 15-20 miles a week. In my late 40s with fairly good, but 40+ year old knees, and I feel like I get excellent support and shock protection from these shoes. Would very highly recommend.

Toegevoegd door Jhont2281 gisteren
View the size chart Become the latest park attraction, turning heads as you race by in the sleek and speedy GT-1000™ from ASICS®! The latest in the GEL-1100™ series. Built for the mild to moderate overpronator who requires a combination of cushioning and stability. Breathable mesh upper. Lightweight synthetic overlays. Seamless design helps reduce chafing. Padded tongue and collar for added comfort. Breathable fabric lining. Removable foam insole for light underfoot cushioning. SpEVA® midsole material maximizes energy return while reducing midsole breakdown. Rearfoot and forefoot Gel® cushioning system attenuates impacting shock and allows for a smooth transition to midstance. DuoMax® Support System is a dual-density midsole that is positioned for optimal support and stability. Trusstic System® reduces overall weight of the sole unit, while retaining the structural integrity of the shoe. Full-length Guidance Line® technology employs a vertical flex groove that decouples the tooling along the line of progression for maximum stride efficiency. DuraSponge® outsole material is comprised of a blown AHAR® (ASICS High Abrasion Rubber) rubber for superior cushioning and long-lasting wear. Imported.
